1061
00:57:28,210 --> 00:57:29,029
Rym: The bell rang.

1062
00:57:29,610 --> 00:57:36,090
Rym: Tim pucked up his books and drifted out into the hallway through the flow of noisy teams, elbowing and clomping toward first-period classes.

1063
00:57:36,570 --> 00:57:39,390
Rym: The odor of chalk dust and floor wax filled the halls.

1064
00:57:39,890 --> 00:57:49,690
Rym: Tim was fantasizing about kicking through a hot game of Double Dragon, Carol Jantz by his side, when he ran smack into Burt Alvin by the boys' room.

1065
00:57:50,533 --> 00:57:51,786
Rym: "It was like running into a

1066
