00:59:03,492 --> 00:59:04,709
Rym: Burt glared at him.

1106
00:59:05,293 --> 00:59:06,268
Rym: "Yeah, I guess so.

1107
00:59:06,691 --> 00:59:09,749
Rym: I don't want you having any accidents while I'm pulverizing

1108
00:59:09,790 --> 00:59:09,870
Rym: you.".

1109
00:59:10,612 --> 00:59:12,310
Rym: "That's, uh, very thoughtful of you, Burt.

1110
00:59:12,650 --> 00:59:14,604
Rym: Which reminds me of a funny joke I heard the other

1111
00:59:14,625 --> 00:59:14,826
Rym: day.".

1112
00:59:15,431 --> 00:59:17,450
Rym: Tim Bradley loved jokes.

1113
00:59:17,851 --> 00:59:18,947
Rym: He loved puns, too.

1114
00:59:19,773 --> 00:59:22,290
Rym: And like he always said, the badder the better.

1115
00:59:22,990 --> 00:59:24,221
Rym: "Why does the chicken cross the

1116
00:59:24,262 --> 00:59:24,746
