01:00:01,450 --> 01:00:04,049
Rym: "Excuse me," said a deep voice from behind him.

1130
01:00:04,291 --> 01:00:05,461
Rym: "Are you Timothy

1131
01:00:05,542 --> 01:00:06,047
Rym: Bradley?".

1132
01:00:06,717 --> 01:00:07,249
Rym: Tim jumped.

1133
01:00:07,850 --> 01:00:09,770
Rym: Startled, he looked up into the mirror.

1134
01:00:10,450 --> 01:00:19,810
Rym: Standing behind him was a tall, blonde-haired man who looked like a superhero from a comic book, only with short hair and a vulnerable, perplexed look on his face.

1135
01:00:20,510 --> 01:00:23,350
Rym: But boy, his costume sure wasn't from anything this century.

1136
01:00:23,890 --> 01:00:30,370
Rym: He wore what looked like a handmade sheep's wool jacket and trousers with a sackcloth shirt cinched at the waist by a wide leather belt.

1137
01:00:30,970 --> 01:00:35,870
Rym: His black boots were leather as well, and he smelled distinctly of garlic.

1138
01:00:36,511 --> 01:00:37,428
Rym: "Uh, yeah, that's me.

1139
01:00:37,811 --> 01:00:38,722
Rym: What is this, Halloween

1140
01:00:38,762 --> 01:00:39,066
Rym: already?".

1141
01:00:39,835 --> 01:00:40,824
Rym: "May I introduce

1142
01:00:40,905 --> 01:00:41,410
Rym: myself?".

1143
01:00:42,111 --> 01:00:43,910
Rym: Tim noted a distinct accent.

1144
01:00:44,556 --> 01:00:46,050
Rym: "I am Simon Belmont.

1145
01:00:46,430 --> 01:00:50,730
Rym: I have come here to your dimension to seek your help with a dreadfully important quest.

1146
01:00:51,210 --> 01:00:52,430
Rym: The fate of Castlevania.

1147
01:00:52,930 --> 01:00:58,348
Rym: To say nothing of my soul, my life, and the soul and life of the woman I love are at

1148
01:00:58,489 --> 01:00:58,790
